    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Glamorous or Gilligan? The Capri Debate</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Karen Bleier letter defends capri pants against criticism in May 31 Op-Ed article; cartoon</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Jennifer Moses (Op-Ed, May 31) is right: Capri pants, though they are ubiquitous this summer, flatter very few women. I tried them, but quickly found that there is a fine line between Laura Petrie and Gilligan.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Jennifer Moses (Op-Ed, May 31) is right: Capri pants, though they are ubiquitous this summer, flatter very few women. I tried them, but quickly found that there is a fine line between Laura Petrie and Gilligan.</p>
        <p>I wanted to look like Laura; I looked like Gilligan.</p>
        <p>KATHLEEN MILLS  Bloomington, Ind., May 31, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
